{
  "texts": [
    "However, the potential impact of executives on strategic decisions and outcomes for their firms and beyond is enormous.",
    "The mandate of executives is to ensure that their firm continues to create value by extending or securing its competitive position.",
    "Such a mandate equips executives with the ability to change a firm's strategic orientation and ways of creating value, affecting not only business outcomes but also outcomes relevant to employees, customers, and society.",
    "Assessing how AI can create value should be a top priority of an executive (Shollo et al., 2022; Wamba-Taguimdje et al., 2020).",
    "Therefore, executives' tasks include continuously assessing a firm's AI orientation and AI implementation ability, contributing to value creation (Li et al., 2021; Weber et al., 2022)."
  ]
}